        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 8:30PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 830 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from near Cass City to near Dryden to near Livonia.
Movement was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Anchorville, Harsens Island, Armada, Deckerville, Shelby Township,
Yale, Capac, Amador, Ray Center, Juhl, Utica, New Greenleaf,
Lexington, Emmett, Fort Gratiot, Marine City, Fargo, Peck, Forester,
and St. Clair.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
